# Address Book Management System — Running Guide

---

## 1. Compilation

To compile the application, navigate to the project root directory (`Address-Book`) and run:

```bash
gcc -Wall -Wextra -Iinclude src/main.c src/contact.c src/file.c -o addressbook
```

*Note: If compiling from inside the `src/` directory, use:*
```bash
gcc -Wall -Wextra -I../include main.c contact.c file.c -o addressbook
```

---

## 2. Running the Application

After compiling, you can run the executable from the project root directory:

```bash
./addressbook
```
